      "date": "2011-07-22 07:07:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI don't think it will cause `hole' in the RPC, because osc_send_oap_rpc() will quit immediately if it finds the page is not started from 0.\n\n                /* If there is a gap at the start of this page, it can't merge\n                 * with any previous page, so we'll hand the network a\n                 * \"fragmented\" page array that it can't transfer in 1 RDMA */\n                if (page_count != 0 && oap->oap_page_off != 0)\n                        break;\n\nThis patch is not complex at all, just less than 10 LoC change(others are for debug). The problem of 1st patch is that the precondition is a bit too strong.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
